<body>
    <div class="document">
        <h1>Galaxy Data Analysis -
    <a target="_blank" href="http://www.princeton.edu/genomics">Lewis-Sigler Institute for Integrative Genomics</a>
    </h1>
    {% if env == 'development' %}
    <div class="errormessagelarge section" id="development-notice">
        <h1>DEVELOPMENT SERVER</h1>
        <h3>ALL DATA IS SUBJECT TO REMOVAL WITHOUT NOTICE!</h3>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="infomessagelarge section" id="updates">
        <h2>What's New</h2>

        <h3>Galaxy Release 17.05</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Tag your data with propagating hashtags</strong>
                <p>Large Galaxy histories used to be messy. Hashtags make it easy to track dataset
                    (and collection) relationships. These two movies (both under a minute) explain
                    how to use this <a href="https://vimeo.com/216884518">with datasets</a> and <a href="https://vimeo.com/216895965">with collections.</a></p>
                <p>Learn more about Galaxy histories in our updated <a href="https://galaxyproject.org/tutorials/histories/">tutorial</a></p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Drag &amp; Drop datasets into tool inputs</strong>
                <p>Interface now allows dragging datasets from history panel into the content selectors
                    of the tool form. Implemented in <a href="https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/pull/3871">Pull Request 3871</a>.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Upload directly to a collection</strong>
                <p>You can now bypass the history manipulation and upload your data straight into a collection for convenience.</p>
                <p>Learn more about collections and how to use them in a new <a href="https://galaxyproject.org/tutorials/collections/">tutorial</a>.</p>
            </li>

            <li>Many other enchancements and fixes, see
                <a href="https://docs.galaxyproject.org/en/master/releases/17.05_announce.html">May 2017 Galaxy Release (v17.05)</a>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Questions, comments, suggestions?</h3>
        <p>
            <a href="mailto:{{ crontab_mailto }}">{{ crontab_mailto }}</a>
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>New tools (custom tools are welcome!)</li>
            <li>Reference genomes and other annotations</li>
            <li>New data sources</li>
            <li>Get help developing analysis pipelines for your lab</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="donemessagelarge section" id="instructions">
    <h2>Getting Started with Galaxy</h2>
    <p>Get started by selecting
    <strong>Get Data</strong> from the menu on the left. Upload a file from
                    your computer or import sequencing data from HTSEQ.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <a href="http://main.g2.bx.psu.edu/galaxy101">Galaxy 101: Tutorial explaining the galaxy basics</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>Watch
                            <a href="http://galaxycast.org/">Screencasts</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>Get an overview of the most useful tools at the
                            <a href="http://www.princeton.edu/genomics/sequencing/instructions/data-analysis/galaxy/">Sequencing Core's Galaxy Overview</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>Read about technical details on the
                            <a href="http://wiki.g2.bx.psu.edu/">Galaxy Wiki</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>Join the
                            <a href="https://sites.google.com/site/princetonhtseq/">Princeton HTSEQ Users Group</a>,
                            discuss, present, and learn from other users in the Princeton research community</li>
                        <li>Get expert advice from the
                            <a href="http://www.princeton.edu/genomics/sequencing/">Lewis-Sigler Sequencing Core Facility</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>
    <a target="_blank" href="https://sites.google.com/site/princetonhtseq/tutorials/snp-and-indel-detection">SNP and Indel Detection Data Analysis Guide</a>
    </h3>
                    <p>A guide for SNP and Indel analysis that includes a step-by-step guide using
                        Galaxy as well as a discussion of various options and considerations when analyzing
                        data including visualization, mapping reads, and working with VCF files.</p>
                    <h3>
    <a target="_blank" href="http://sites.google.com/site/princetonhtseq/tutorials/rna-seq">RNA-Seq Data Analysis Guide</a>
    </h3>
                    <p>A step-by-step guide using Galaxy as well as some things to consider such as
                        handling replicates, reads that map to multiple places, and additional software
                        tools.
                    </p>
                    <h3>
    <a target="_blank" href="http://sites.google.com/site/princetonhtseq/tutorials/chip-seq">ChIP-Seq Data Analysis Guide</a>
    </h3>
                    <p>A step-by-step guide to using Galaxy as well as a considerations regarding replicates,
                        reads that map to multiple places, and additional software tools.</p>

        </div>

        <div class="errormessagelarge section" id="diskspace-notice">
            <h2>Disk Space is Limited</h2>
            <h3>Please delete datasets you no longer need to make room for others</h3>
            <p>By viewing your list of saved histories, you can see how much space each is taking
                up. Please delete any histories that you no longer need. Your cooperation is
                appreciated.
            </p>
            <h3>Data stored for more than 30 days may be deleted without notice.</h3>
        </div>

